<Text>I was very much avoiding using a company like Geo Links because of all the misconceptions out there. I was pursuing Verizon, Charter and the other big name providers. Due to the location of my business I was quoted insane cost for installation, some near $20k to lay fiber in my block. Then I noticed I had a Geo Links satellite on my roof from the previous owner. I made 1 call and they sent the signal over and boom, I was up and running. For a business or home in a similar situation I would absolutely recommend they give Geo Links a try before Viasat/HughesNet. From experience, this service is superior in every way. I've not had 1 problem in the last two years.< /Text>< pictures>

<user_id>104377282419443045002< /user_id><user_name>Paul H<//user_name>< Date>
1442001072261<//Date>
< Rating>
1</Rating>
< Review>
Our family was taking a trip from CA to Phoenix for the Labor day weekend. We wanted to break up the drive and Palm Springs is roughly the half-way point. We were looking for a reasonably priced and well-reviewed property and settled on International Lodge.

We got a late start and called the property to advise them that we would be arriving late in the evening or maybe even very early in the AM. At that point, for the first time, we were advised that the office is not open 24/7 and that they normally close at 10pm.

The woman at the front desk was very gracious though and told us she would keep the office open until midnight and advise the GM (who I presume lives on-property) that we would be arriving late for an after-hours check-in. We advised her that we would call again when we had a better idea about our ETA.

We called back at 11:30 and told them we would be arriving at approximately 12:30-12:40am. The woman at the desk re-iterated what she'd already told us, that the office would be closed but that the GM was aware we'd be arriving late and wanting an after-hours ck in. She made sure we knew to call the after-hours number posted at the office.

We finally arrive at 12:30 am and called the after-hours number as directed. A dozen times.

With my wife and 5 1/2 month old son in the car, I sat in the parking lot and called the GM 12 times, leaving 7 messages and got no response.

After an hour of this we decided to leave. Before doing so we called the third-party that we booked through; they attempted to relocate us to another property but were unable to do so.

At that point we figured our best option was to hunker down and just drive straight-through to AZ. However, we found a Hampton Inn back close to the hwy that saved our bacon with an available room.

We did finally get a call back from the GM--20 minutes after I'd left my last message. I did not answer it as we were in the process of attempting to get the room at Hampton Inn. The GM did not leave a message and we have not heard anything from him by phone or mail in the week since.

The third-party requested a refund on our behalf but we were advised that the hotel refused the request because the room was a)non refundable and b) "had been held for the guest".

There is nothing positive for me to say about this experience or the property. While the photos and description make it sound like a nice place to stay--and it may be--based on our experience I can't ever recommend a stay here.

It's not even that we received horrible service. We received no service at all.</Review>

102918253898437847981</UserId.>
< Name>
Rodney S< /Name>
< date>
1609138392575<//date>
<rating>4< /rating>< Text>
Getting our kicks by shopping for new kicks

*Social Distancing review*

I've been wearing Skechers Performance Go Walk 3 Compete shoes, w/ the Goga Mat Goga Pillars, for years.  They're light, comfy, springy, and an all around great active walking shoe.  I had a Citadel Outlets gift card, so we stopped by Skechers at the Citadel Outlets to see what they had for sale.

For months, I've had my internet eyes on the Go Walk 5 Wistful, which are Skechers Velcro shoes.  Same type of shoe I've been rocking, but with Velcro straps, instead of laces.  I find Velcro to be a better fit, and much easier to put on.  So, I forged a path into the Citadel Outlets store looking for them.  Alas, no luck.  I asked a staffer if they had it, again, met with no luck.  I also had some interest in the Skechers Work Moltke waterproof pull on boots, but after finding & purchasing some really comfortable Columbia Grove Heights Outdry waterproof shoes, at the nearby Columbia store for $30 less, I didn't bother searching for them.

Although, I didn't end up purchasing anything for myself, I did purchase a couple slip on shoes for my mom.  There was a Buy One, Get One 60% off promotion, so my mom wanted to take advantage of that.

Service was good.  I asked the aforementioned staffer about the particular shoe I was looking for, and she was quick to provide assistance.  I asked another staffer to help with my mom, and she was also friendly & helpful.  Finally, the young man working the register was also hospitable.

Skechers is centrally located towards the middle of the Citadel Outlets.

I'm by no means a male Imelda Marcos, but there's something about buying new shoes.  And the staff at the Citadel Outlets Skechers made it as painless as possible.  I'm a Skechers fan, and seeing how I still have money on my Citadel Outlets gift card, it's a given I'll be back, hopefully with the Go Walk 5 Wistful in stock, as I'll take it home in a heartbeat.

Highly recommend!< /Text>

<Rate>5</Rate><Review>We went to get my mom some shoes. The closes store is in south gate so we decided to go there. As we walked in there were  3 employees all of them inside the register. We didn't get greeted when we were inside. We finally found the shoe style we wanted and my husband had to go to the register and ask if they had it in the size we were looking for. They didn't. So he asked if they could check if another store had it and her response was...."we can order it for you". He got on Google called the store in Lynnwood and trough the phone they told him the one in the citadel had it. We then called citadel and they placed the shoe on hold. There was only 1 other customer in the store and didn't see any of three employees say a word to her. They all just stood in the register.

We went to the store at the citadel and we're greeted as we approached the door. While my husband was in line one of the employees went around asking if anyone needed help. As we left the store we were thanked for stopping buy. Thank you Karen for your help.

So if you are looking for shoes save yourself some time and drive out to the citadel. Where they can actually help you find a stye, where they actually greet you and where you are appreciated for your business.< /Review><pics>None<//pics>< Resp>

< rate>
4<//rate>
<Review>I was allowed in the lobby of the dentist office and I was asked a few health questions which I answered, then the assistant took my temperature with a swipe motion past my forehead. When I asked what my temperature was she said 88.2. I said that's kind of low isn't it and she said yes. I had never heard of a body temperature that low so I was somewhat worried and asked the hygienist about it when I was in the room. She said she didn't think it was anything to worry about. She cleaned my teeth, then I consulted with Dr. Tran, and then I left. Thinking of my teeth only I forgot to ask him about my body temperature. When I got home I looked it up online and found that anything under 92 degrees was very serious hypothermia, even life threatening. Symptoms of hypothermia would be shivering and exhaustion, confusion, memory loss drowsiness or slurred speech.  Alarmed by this information and wondering if I needed to go into ER immediately, I got my own digital thermometer and took my temperature. It was 98.8. I took it several more times and it was always in the 98 plus range. Not experiencing any of the symptoms of hypothermia I realized that the dental assistant must have taken my temperature in error.  I would just like to let the staff know that their temperature taking is not accurate and if they get a temperature such as 88.2 they should recognize that that is very serious and they should double-check their reading.
Other than that my hygienist was very nice and gentle and we were done in about 20 minutes. I do think Manteca Dental prices are pretty high, since I don't have insurance and the cleaning plus a brief consultation with the doctor cost me $182.</Review>< pictures>

<rating>5</rating><review>I first found Hello Bella after Tony gave me his business card while working my 2nd job at Dollar Tree. They WERE looking pretty rough but he was kind enough to not say it! Since they are close to my house and the reviews were good I thought I'd check them out.

From the moment you walk in the door they are all genuinely sweet and attentive. They give you water and a little snack while you wait...which is never long. They make sure you are comfortable and enjoying your visit. The massages they do with the pedicure feel like real massages not just the normal rub down you get at other places. They always remember me and ask about my mom (who's only been once) and my son etc. They really seem to care about their customers!

They have a huge selection of colors, both regular polish and gel. I don't think I've ever seen that large of a gel selection before! Their prices are really reasonable and my nails last 3-4 weeks depending on how hard I am on them.

I am so happy to have found Hello Bella!<//review>< Pics>

<Review>4DX is why I come here its a 30 min drive but worth it for the experience. If you watched a movie in 3D and are amazed wait until you come watch it here in 4D. Yup you get that extra dimension here and it's insane, first off your seat will move you around as if you're in the movie make sure its an action packed movie like Hobbs and Shaw. Expect lighting effects in the theater, wind blasting at you and water, plenty of water that will make you think am I watching this or am I in this movie. If you like fighting scenes expect to feel them so you better be ready for that punch. They have some movie exhibits here so make sure your camera is ready, plus you'll never know who might be walking around here.

My Next movie that I would watch in 4DX is Terminator definitely worth the wait.<//Review>< pictures>

<Review>First time here and I really enjoyed it. My mom and I watched 'Ready or Not' and it was great! I thought I wouldn't be a fan of one scene movies, but this one caught my attention and kept me interested from start to finish. There were five people total and I wasn't mad about it, gave me the chance to use both armrests.

I ordered the 'Spicy chicken sandwich with fries' which was absolutely delicious. The fries are very crispy and the chicken sandwich was good. It was no Chick-fil-A but it still wowed me! The only downfall about this experience is how close the seats are together, I liked the rocking it had, but in the end, it was the closeness that turned me off. I also really appreciated how the huge the screen was. I didn't bring my glasses so I was scared I wouldn't be able to view the movie clearly.

Overall I enjoyed the food and the comforble, clean surrounding this first time experience gave me!

*Police guards check bags before you go inside the theatre*<//Review>< Time>

Service was good overall. Snacks and parking are expensive, but that's the same at every theater.

Heads up: parking is fully automated, so you will need to take your ticket to get validated inside the theater and then pay at a machine in the parking lot before returning to your car.

VIEWS: Okay, that said, the best part of this theater is the views of the city that you get from the huge windows that look northeast. I bet it's gorgeous on a rainy day or just after a storm at sunset. Several floors have these views and these big open waiting spaces are probably a nice for lingering before or after a film with a date. < review>
First time here and I really enjoyed it. My mom and I watched 'Ready or Not' and it was great! I thought I wouldn't be a fan of one scene movies, but this one caught my attention and kept me interested from start to finish. There were five people total and I wasn't mad about it, gave me the chance to use both armrests.

I ordered the 'Spicy chicken sandwich with fries' which was absolutely delicious. The fries are very crispy and the chicken sandwich was good. It was no Chick-fil-A but it still wowed me! The only downfall about this experience is how close the seats are together, I liked the rocking it had, but in the end, it was the closeness that turned me off. I also really appreciated how the huge the screen was. I didn't bring my glasses so I was scared I wouldn't be able to view the movie clearly.

Overall I enjoyed the food and the comforble, clean surrounding this first time experience gave me!

*Police guards check bags before you go inside the theatre*</review>

<review>I just got back home from watching Aquaman, my first movie here at LA LIVE and I thoroughly enjoyed myself. I was able to bypass the horror of handing over my precious money thanks to two free passes I've held on to. So, I can't speak about pricing but I do have a few other comments to share.

There were several bike racks available in front of the box office, which was nice. After entering, a security guard did quickly rustle through my backpack and failed to notice a few snacks I'd left in there. The lobby was very well cleaned and perfect for a few quick snapshots of the LA downtown skyline. The theatre itself was just as it should be, clean, dimly lit, and a bit chilly.

I have only one complaint, the closed door to the men's restroom. You have to physically turn a doorknob to enter and exit. I've seen men all my life walk out the restroom without washing their hands and the thought of sharing a doorknob with them makes me cringe.</review>< pictures>

<Time>1550035361183< /Time>< Text>
I watched Lego Movie 2 here on a Sunday evening.  The front of the movie theater looks pretty cool, especially at night.  Because of that, it is pretty easy to locate.

Theater: Probably the biggest theater I've seen.  The movie was showing in theater 1 and there were probably at most 5 parties watching that night.  The seats are ok, not reclining, so not super comfortable but not too upright.

Concessions:  I wanted to buy popcorn, but after seeing the prices, I decided not to ($7.00 for a small).

Parking: $8 for the first 4 hours with validation.  Too expensive.

Overall, I thought that it was a nice theater.  However, the parking alone kills it for me.  I will probably never return to this cinema just for that reason.  $8 for parking after validation is pretty ridiculous, I would rather drive somewhere an extra 5 miles away to get free parking.</Text>

<GmapID>0x80c2c7b97b8d3083:0x72781c6c65cf5255< /GmapID>< Review>
Theater is very nice, very clean.  It's in affluent new downtown development and the prices match.  Even matinee price of $14 for adult ticket is pricey. Has large full back carpeted chairs which are quite comfortable but tightly packed with narrow isles.  They are not anywhere near as nice, as the super spacious AMC leather recliner chairs and isles, but nice enough you won't be squirming to get comfortable half way through the movie.  Crowded on weekends but midweek never fills up.  Midweek matinee shows often have only one or two couples.  They run specials on Monday's and Tuesdays.  They have a membership program but it's not very generous.</Review>

If could give this theater zero stars I would. I went to see a concert film there last night. Got off work and rushed over, but parking was a hassle because of some event at LA live, so I missed the start time of my 10:40 film by a minute or 2. No problem there I decided to see the 11:40 show instead since I hate missing the beginning.  So I get in early enough and get ready for my movie. It starts and the light don't go down.  I wait patiently because I'm sure someone is monitoring the theater and will fix it. 2 min goes by and nothing now I'm distracted and worried if I don't get up and alert someone it'll just stay lit through the movie. I get up, go out and tell down the hall at the ticket taker, but she ignores me! I go back in and I've already missed most of the beginning. I don't want to go out again because I'll miss even more of the movie, but I can't even concentrate on the movie because the lights are creating a bad viewing experience.  ANOTHER 5 MINTUES GO BY AND NOTHING. I'm trying get someone's attention in the booth peak out the door to see if anyone is coming and yell for help again, nothing. I sit back down, but I've missed even more of the movie. Finally someone comes in and I yell at them about the lights and finally it gets fixed. Meanwhile I'm not paying attention because I'm fuming, I missed a lot of the beginning I was worried about missing anyway. <name>Ryan Caldwell<//name><Date>1533525058701<//Date><Rating>2<//Rating>< Text>
Caught blindspotting last night in theater 7 I believe. Can't speak to the other theaters, but the house itself is too small. The rows are overly steep, and unless you're in the back the rows, you're craning your head up to watch the picture. In the same sense, the distance from projection to screen is short leaving the majority of the rows too close to the screen for proper scope. The film presentation suffers for this.
POOR Theater design, probably meant to cram more cinemas into the complex, ruins the experience. Lacking multiple senses of space, I won't be going back.
Additionally, with validation, parking is still expensive.
And Searching bags to watch a movie? What kind of guest experience are they really offering? I don't know what kind of issues they're trying to prevent, but it now includes patronage.
All around let down.< /Text>

< Review>
Like always, the movie theatre was awesome, big, clean, and just great in general. I love regal. However, I gave it 3 stars based on my experience yesterday. The employee at the concession stand rounded up my bill of $24.12 to make $25, donating the $.88 to "charity". I have no problem donating but I was never asked if I wanted to donate. Regardless of the amount or purpose of this money that was taken without my permission, I feel like the money was stolen from me because I never said yes to a donation. 0x80c2c7b97b8d3083:0x72781c6c65cf5255</gmap_id>
<Review>Always enjoy this theatre. The auditoriums are great offering 3D, 4D, and there are premium auditoriums with jumbo screens and amazing acoustics. The "regular" auditoriums are also just fine.  They feature  all of the latest and greatest movies, often host movie premieres, and occasionally will screen other cool features such as live concerts on screen.  There are always multiple showtimes, and they keep popular movies screening for a good amount of time. They offer some great deals when you have a Regal Club card (free), and other nice promos!  The customer service is generally efficient, and pleasant.  Just keep in mind parking can get expensive, and for Pete sakes never, ever lose your validation card or you're paying full price ($27 daily rate).  If you travel by transit or Uber, it might be preferable and cost-efficient, and after the movie you can enjoy carousing around LA Live a bit, a nice wrap-up for the night.  Enjoy!<//Review><UserId.>100689290286683801212< /UserId.>< Resp>
None</Resp>

1399610399586<//Time>
<name>CherryLosAngeles</name>< Text>
This is a great theatre for the reason that it's HUGE!  The design takes advantage of the large lot of land and is well .... regal with lots of open space, three floors of movies/snack stands, plenty of rest rooms, party rooms and ticket windows so you never have to wait.  It brings to mind old fashioned one movie house theatres where going to see a movie was an event.

I like the design since I've attend festivals at the Regal DTLA and it never feels claustrophobic no matter how many people are around.  LA Live has tons of pay parking and street parking with meters as well as a variety of places where you can grab dinner/drinks.  I like that since it's super large they have a great mix of mainstream films as well as indie/genre films that usually won't be shown at mainstream movie houses.<//Text>

<resp>None< /resp>< review>
The tickets were regular price, though the food, of course, as expected of any movie theater was way overpriced and just edible enough to satisfy...some. The seats were comfy enough, though for someone as short as me it was a bit uncomfortable as my legs couldn't touch the ground and the seat kept trying to snap closed every time I moved. The sound quality was perfect though and as long as you got a seat somewhere in the middle, near the front, you had a pretty good view of the screen.

The bathroom facilities were good for a public bathroom, though that doesn't mean that there won't be--accidents--from time to time. And anyone who ever thought that the women's restrooms were ever cleaner than the men's has obviously never visited one. One thing I would have appreciated though, would have been more seating arrangements in the lobby. I don't know about you but for those of us who don't have our own form of transportation at the moment and are eagerly awaiting to be picked up, it's nice to be able to sit down and watched the view outside comfortably.< /review>

< Name>

< time>
1547619321162<//time>
<rate>4<//rate><text>In town for a convention and needed decided to see Venom on a whim.

I downloaded the Regal app, created an account and purchased a ticket to Venom in under 10 minutes.   $29.99 for the 4DX theater experience.  I've heard of it but was finally going to check out this 4DX.

I entered the theater, showed them my mobile ticket, got scanned and I was off to my 4DX theater.  4DX has assigned seating fyi.

Your 4DX theater chair moves like a motion control ride at Universal Studios throughout the whole movie.  You'll also get vibrations, water sprays, fogs, scents and auxiliary strobe lights on the walls.  There is a lot of movement and it might not be for everyone during the length of a movie. After describing all that, I loved it!  Couple all this along with the 4D glasses and I got a movie experience I've never had before and will definitely try again.  All those elements were orchestrated well with the movie Venom and I would love to try 4DX with another action movie.

Overall, I had a great experience at Regal LA Live and I'd definitely check out their 4DX theater again if given the chance.  Enjoy..!</text><Pictures>None<//Pictures><Resp>None<//Resp>< gmap_id>

We soon became overhear the theater was busted and it had been since yesterday.  They can't have sent an email or something?  I live about 45 minutes away.  If anyone knows the kind of hellish traffic that goes on downtown after work will have a little empathy with me.  Anyways, we waited for about 15 to 20 minutes to be "greeted" by whatever type of manager to be asked do you want a refund.  No, sorry about the inconvienence and explanation for what's happening.  I mean, I have a little sympathy for this guy because of all the upset customers he has to go through.  He also asked if we wanted to see it in a different theater. < text>
As a movie lover and resident nearby this place, it is good place but not an awesome place. Don't get this wrong! I love this place.  But let just look at this place objectively. First, the price! the price is slightly expensive than other theaters. Also they have called 4D experience which is the chair vibrating for some moment.... quite disappointed compare to the price they offer....  Maybe I expected too much. I was expecting like the chairs from the Universal Studio. Therefore, if you have a low expectation of 4D, then go for it!! But if you have a high expectation like me, I suggest you should take 3D or just regular 2D. Second, if you drive, the parking is also one of your concern, unless you are willing to pay a lot. For me, first time I visit here I was expecting free parking for movie, but there is no that kind of service. So I recommend you to come here by Uber. Finally, subtitles!! whenever I hang out with Chinese or Korean friends, they prefer AMC in some location or CGV in ktown. Bcz they offer Chinese or Korean subtitle service. I believe if Regal has a similar service then there will be more movie watchers.
FYI, there are also a lot of nice bars and restaurants nearby. I guess it is good place to watch a moive after dine with your girlfrend or boyfriend.</text>

PARKING
REGAL CINEMAS - LOT 4 When attending a movie at Regal Cinemas L.A. LIVE Stadium 14, we strongly recommend parking in Lot 4* located on the north side of Olympic Boulevard at Georgia Street. Regal Cinemas will validate parking for ticketed guests.

If Lot 4 is full, please use the West Garage (Lot W) Gates E and F only.

NOTE: One validation per vehicle is allowed.

Lot 4 Parking Rates (with Regal L.A. LIVE validation)
$8 = First 4 hours (or fraction thereof)

Lot 4 Parking Rates (without validation)
$10 = First 2 hours
$10 = Each additional ¬Ω hour (or fraction thereof, $28 maximum

Flat Rate
$15 = Cars entering after 9:00 p.m. and exiting before 4:30 a.m.<//Text></record>

< Text>
What a scam. $27 for parking at the parking garage closest to Regal Cinemas. I got to the parking garage a little after 9pm.  Met a friend at a nearby restaurant, then after we went to see a movie at Regal. I validated my ticket for parking and when I put it in the machine to pay it was $27. I went back to the theater to double check if my ticket was validated correctly and the Regal Cinemas employee behind the guest services said $27 was correct and there was nothing he could do. This is an excessive charge for under 5 hours parking with validation.  I've been here countless times since this theater opened and this was a first. Maybe this movie was 30 minutes longer than other movies I've seen in the past. Still, no reason to charge this much to park. The parking cost more than the movie ticket. There are many places like Arclight in Hollywood  ($3 parking with validation) OR Landmark Theaters in West Los Angeles  (Free Parking) to choose from. No wonder so many people getting in and out of Uber and Lyft cars in front of Regal. A place can scam someone one time if they only want your business one time. I hope Regal changes this high cost for parking. The parking should not be more expensive than the movie</Text>

< Rating>
4</Rating>
<review>I have been to the 4DX room twice for Terminator Genisys and San Andreas. I love that the only one in the nation is in Los Angeles. The room itself feels high tech and makes for a great movie-going experience. The seats, when not in motion, are much more rigid than your average movie theater seat. The experience really depends on which movie you're seeing but it can definitely make an average movie more exciting. I haven't been to the other screening rooms but I imagine them to also be nice as the lobby is always clean. The staff so far have been great.

The major downside is parking. They don't really have their own lot so you have to either park across the street or at the structure closer to Staples. Even with validation you still have to pay around $6. Since it's in downtown and around other major attractions I understand why it can be lacking in this department which is why this theater doesn't have a perfect rating. I would come again for special occasions and the 4DX theater.<//review><Pics>None</Pics><Response>None</Response>< gmapID>

Laura S< /user_name>

0x80c2c7b97b8d3083:0x72781c6c65cf5255<//gmapID>
< review>
What I like about this theater is that they tend to have cool settings from the movies for photo ops. I was just here for Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and they had "The Lair" set up made of pizza boxes and such. So I took tons of photos here.

Another thing I like about this theater... the 4D theater! It does feel like you're in the movie. I know not a lot of people liked TMNT, but the 4D really brought out the fun of it. I wish I saw Guardians with the 4D.

4D Theater:
The seats are comfy but you need to be sitting with both feet on the ground to really appreciate it. I'm very twitchy, so I need to switch butt sides... yeah, I'm weird. But I just do. It gets tired. Also, you have the option to not be sprayed by water with a button.
For the loverbirds, it's hard to hold hands and put your arms around each other in these seats. Sorry.

SERVICE: No problems.

PARKING:
Park in the East side. They don't validate for West.
$5 with validation<//review>

<Review>I have never had issues with this movie theater till today! I was supposed to watch Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom in 4DX at 10:30AM. I arrived on time and found a seat. The screen was blank for 20 min before an employee came out to let us know they were experiencing technical difficulties with the projector and that they would restart it, skip the previews & start with the film in 5 min. Cool! 20 min later they let us know that they had to cancel the 10:30 show & would issue refunds to all. I've experienced this once before here and the manager gave me the option to watch it on a regular projector (2D) as well as gave me a 4DX ticket to use as I pleased at a later date. Not this time! I asked the manager what I was getting besides just a refund. She said nothing! I mentioned what happened last time & she said nothing could be done since it's Tuesday (they have discounted shows Tuesdays)! I redeemed 15,000 Regal credits toward the show & asked her if those would be credited to my account, which she of course said yes! I still don't see the 15,000 credits I redeemed back in my account. It took me 30 min to get from Inglewood to Downtown LA, 40 min watching a blank screen, 20 min to get a refund & another 30 min to get back home. So I spent 2 hours of my life with nothing to show but less gas in my car! Sadly, Regal knows they're the only 4DX theater in LA & could careless about it's customers, or at least the manager today! I may have to go back to watching movies in IMAX or trying Cinemark XD theaters. Very disappointed!!!<//Review>< pics>
